help my kitten has a hernia we just got a three week old kitten and when we brought her home we found a dime sized bubble on her belly my mom said it looked like a hernia but she doesn't know what to do for it so my questions are what is it what do i do for it is it contagious will it go away and does it hurt her any explanation would be great thanks a hernia is a hole in the muscles of the abdomen in the case of your kitten it's probably because the hole from her umbilical cord hasn't properly healed her internal organs will slip out through that hole and sit between the skin and muscle which is very dangerous don't try to do anything instead get her to a vet asap this is a life threatening condition for your kitten if you don't have a vet fix it she will die also discuss how to care for a three week old kitten a kitten that small should not be away from her mother she needs her diet supplemented with kitten formula not infant formula kitten formula bought at a pet store or gotten from your vet now get off the computer and get your mom to call the vet good luck Hernia Ferret Androgen insensitivity syndrome Abdomen Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Guinea pig Childbirth Cat Garfield Cryptorchidism Phoebe Buffay's songs Pet skunk Cephalic disorder Umbilicus Obstetrics Socialization Fecal incontinence Fancy rat Urinary incontinence Kitten Gastroesophageal reflux disease Hamster Spina bifida Tuberculosis Atomic Kitten Prostate cancer Theory of conduct Aquatic ape hypothesis Sexual reproduction Pet store Inguinal hernia The Marshall Mathers LP Microchip implant (animal) Equine conformation Head Feral cat Syringomyelia Thermoregulation Kurt Cobain First aid Sin City StarCraft: Hybrid Dieting RuneScape quests Breech birth Smallpox Stomach cancer Domestic rabbit Stem cell Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Traumatic brain injury Medicine Epilepsy Poker jargon Muscle Stopping power Menstrual cup Liver Intelligence quotient My Life as a Teenage Robot Premature birth Umbilical cord Professiona